parametertype.description: Bearer QCI. New entry each time the QCI changes. Format: [ {TIMESTAMP: QCI} …} ]

parametertype.name: BEARER_ACTIVATION_LIST
parametertype.description: Every Attach and Service Request procedure stored in text format. Format: [ {TIMESTAMP: TYPE: PAGING: RESULT} …} ] The PAGING parameter indicates if the SERVICE_REQUEST was initiated by the network (TRUE) or the UE (FALSE)

parametertype.name: UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE_LIST
parametertype.description: Every UeContextRelease procedure information stored in text format. Format: [ {TIMESTAMP: TriggerNode: S1ReleaseCause: ReleaseCause} … ]

parametertype.name: RSRP_RSRQ_LIST
parametertype.description: The actual RSRP measurement values in dBm from the first cell in the report. See 3GPP 36.331. This values are stored in following format: [ {time-1:rsrp-1:rsrq-1} {time-2:rsrp-2:rsrq-2} {time-3:rsrp-3:rsrq-3} ]

parametertype.name: HO_LIST
parametertype.description: Every hand over procedure information stored in text format. Format: [ {TIMESTAMP: RESULT: TYPE: ENB_CAUSE_CODE: MME_CAUSE_CODE: MME_SUB_CAUSE_CODE} … ] A new entry is stored for each attempted handover. In cases where the handover failed all the cause codes are populated from the LTE_HANDOVER correlated event.

parametertype.name: RSRP_MEDIAN
parametertype.description: The RSRP measurement result the first cell in the report. See 3GPP 36.331. The RSRP values are classified into 3 different categories and those are 1(BEST),2(NEUTRAL), 3(POOR). This classification is based on the algorithm defined below. RSRP > -75dBm(66) => 1 (BEST) RSRP between -75dBm(65) and -95dBm(46) => 2 (NEUTRAL) RSRP > -95dBm(45) => 3 (BAD)

parametertype.name: RSRQ_MEDIAN
parametertype.description: The RSRQ measurement result the first cell in the report. See 3GPP 36.331. The RSRQ values are classified into 3 different categories and those are 1(BEST),2(NEUTRAL), 3(POOR). This classification is based on the algorithm defined below. RSRQ > -9dBm(22) => 1 (BEST) RSRQ between -9dBm(21) and -12dBm(16) => 2 (NEUTRAL) RSRQ > -12dBm(15) => 3 (BAD)

parametertype.name: CQI_REPORTED
parametertype.description: Every CQI Reported value for the user stored in text format. Every CQI reported in the INTERNAL_PER_RADIO_UE_MEASUREMENT periodic events are stored with the following Format [ {CQI Report 1} {CQI Report 2} ... ]: Where each CQI Report is in the format: { long: long: long: ... }

parametertype.name: TCP_RTT_TX_TO_RX
parametertype.description: The Median Round Trip Time at microsecond precision observed on the last acknowledged packet per flow on all the users connection.

parametertype.name: TCP_RTT_AT_HS
parametertype.description: The Median Round Trip Time at microsecond precision observed on the establishment (Hand Shake) of all connections for this user.

parametertype.name: TCP_VOLUME
parametertype.description: The total number of KiloBytes observed on all flows for the given user.

parametertype.name: TCP_UNIQUE_RETX_PKTS
parametertype.description: The number of unique retransmitted packets. The packets could be retransmitted for a number of reasons e.g. lost, corrupt, late response or received reject

parametertype.name: TCP_UNIQUE_RETX_PKTS
parametertype.description: The number of unique retransmitted packets. The packets could be retransmitted for a number of reasons e.g. lost, corrupt, late response or received reject

parametertype.name: PROTOCOL_GROUP
parametertype.description: The protocol group of a flow as determined by the classifier in use, see the documentation of the classifier to interpret this parameter.

parametertype.name: CLS_APPLICATION
parametertype.description: The application of a flow as determined by the classifier in use, see the documentation of the classifier to interpret this parameter.

event.name: S1_HANDOVER

event.comment: This event is an aggregation of the events that happen in UE Triggered Service Request and Network Triggered Service Request

event.name: LTE_CALL_DROP
event.comment: This event is an aggregation of the events that happen in UE Context Release

event.name: INITIAL_ATTACH
event.comment: This event is an aggregation of the events that happen in UE ATTACH procedure

event.name: NET_TG_SERVICE_REQUEST_CORR
event.comment: This event is an aggregation of the events that happen in Network Triggered Service Request and Network Triggered Service Request

event.name: LTE_USER_SESSION
event.comment: This event is an aggregation of the events that happen in user plane session correlation

event.name: LTE_CALL_SETUP_FAILURE
event.comment: This event details a LTE Call setup failure i.e. cases where the ENodeB does not produce the expected sequence of events: INTERNAL_PROC_RRC_CONN_SETUP, INTERNAL_PROC_S1_SIG_CONN_SETUP and INTERNAL_PROC_INITIAL_CTXT_SETUP. Or when we have the Radio Events but no matching Core event

event.name: LTE_ERAB_SESSION
event.comment: This event is an aggregation of the events that happen in bearer session
